TeleConnect ML Assignment Report
1. Problem Statement
The goal of this project is to analyze customer data and solve two key business problems:
•	Predict whether a customer will churn (Classification)
•	Estimate customer revenue (Regression)
________________________________________
2. Dataset Description
The dataset used is the Telco Customer Churn dataset from Kaggle.
•	Total Records: 7043
•	Features: 21
•	Includes customer details like tenure, monthly charges, contract type, etc.
________________________________________
3. Data Preprocessing
•	Converted TotalCharges to numeric format
•	Removed missing values
•	Encoded categorical variables using one-hot encoding
•	Dropped unnecessary columns like customerID
________________________________________
4. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
•	Visualized churn distribution
•	Analyzed relationships between features
•	Used correlation heatmap to understand feature importance
________________________________________
5. Models Used
🔹 Classification Models
•	Logistic Regression
•	Random Forest
🔹 Regression Models
•	Linear Regression
•	Random Forest Regressor
________________________________________
6. Results
Classification:
•	Best Model: Random Forest
•	ROC-AUC Score: ~0.92
Regression:
•	Best Model: Random Forest Regressor
•	RMSE: ~ 1.5
________________________________________
7. Key Insights
•	Customers with low tenure are more likely to churn
•	High monthly charges increase churn probability
•	Long-term customers generate stable revenue
________________________________________
8. Conclusion
This project successfully applied machine learning techniques to predict customer churn and estimate revenue.
Random Forest performed best for both classification and regression tasks. The insights gained from this analysis can help businesses improve customer retention and revenue planning.

